# Data integrity

## Raw data is immutable
- Files under `Data/` follow the layout in `Data/MASTER_DATA.md`. **Never overwrite in place.**
- New curated outputs go under `reports/panels/` (Parquet) or `reports/tables/` (CSV). Never under `Data/`.
- Filenames are dated: `<dataset>__<freq>__<YYYY-MM-DD>.csv`.

## Date handling
- All dates parsed as UTC (`pd.to_datetime(..., utc=True)`). No naive timestamps.
- Default calendar is `calendar_daily` from `config/calendars.yml`. Any deviation MUST state the calendar explicitly.
- Forward-fill is allowed ONLY when `calendars.yml` permits it for that frequency. Otherwise use the missingness taxonomy (`src/cqresearch/data/missingness.py`).

## Join discipline
- Join keys: a single `date` column, sorted ascending, no duplicates. Assert with `df.index.is_monotonic_increasing and df.index.is_unique`.
- Before any `merge`, log left/right row counts, join key overlap, and missingness per column.

## Numeric conventions
- Returns are log-returns `np.log(P_t / P_{t-1})` unless a function name ends in `_simple_return`.
- Percent values are stored as decimals (0.05 not 5.0). Label units in column names (`..._bps`, `..._pct`).
- Never silently cast `int64` to `float64` on a merge. Cast explicitly.

## Reproducibility
- Every script emits a `reports/run_summaries/<date>_<script>.md` with: git commit, params, row counts in/out, hash of output file.
